<div class="content_container main_container mobile_padding">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <h2>Security</h2>
            <p>Halifax Shopping Centre’s Security works 24 hours a day, 365 days a year to provide a safe and enjoyable environment for our customers.&nbsp; &nbsp;The Security department has 13 full-time security officers, two supervisors and one manager.&nbsp; Along with close circuit television surveillance, and crime prevention and intervention, our security personal is responsible for:</p>
            <ul>
            <li>Assisting customers with locations of vehicles;</li>
            <li>Providing first aid for injuries or illnesses.&nbsp; Our security staff are trained in CPR, First Aid and use of on-site defibrillators;</li>
            <li>Locating lost children;</li>
            <li>Operating a lost and found property program</li>
            <li>Ensuring personal safety through escorts and constant, uniformed patrols using a marked security vehicle and bike seasonal bicycle patrols;</li>
            <li>Providing battery boosts. (Security can assist in directly all other vehicle problems to a tow truck company.)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Our Security acts as an important link to Halifax Regional Police and other emergency services that may be required at Halifax Shopping Centre.&nbsp; &nbsp;If you require security assistant, please visit their office on the upper level next to Roots.&nbsp; Customer Service, located on the lower level across from La Senza, can also contact them for you.</p>
            <p><a href="http://d33wyx0pza9yj4.cloudfront.net/sites/5438407c6e6f64462d020000/58e59d04617f358607587f54457834b7/HSC-Mall-Rules.pdf">Halifax Shopping Centre Safety and Security Policies</a></p>
            <h3>Employment</h3>
            <p> Are you interested in working as a member of the Halifax Shopping Centre Security Service?&nbsp; If so, please submit your resume and cover letter, specifying if you desire part-time or full-time, to the security office.&nbsp; Resumes are accepted on a continuous basis, with interviews held as positions become available.&nbsp; Security experience and post-secondary education (particularly in Law and Security or Police Foundation) is preferred,&nbsp; but not required.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    $(document).ready(function(e){
        init(e);
        function renderAll(){
            var pathArray = window.location.pathname.split( '/' );
            var slug = pathArray[pathArray.length-1];
            prefix = get_prefix();
            var pages_json = prefix+ "/pages/halifaxcentre-security.json"
            $.getJSON(pages_json).done(function(data) {
                $('#mm_page_title').html(data.title.toUpperCase());
                $('#mm_page_content').html(data.body);
            }).fail(function(jqXHR) {
                if (jqXHR.status == 404) {
                    $("#404_msg").fadeIn("fast");
                }
            }); 
            show_content();
        }
        loadMallDataCached(renderAll); 
    })
</script>